# Gingerbread Cookies

> A classic holiday treat, gingerbread cookies are spiced, sweet, and perfect for festive occasions. Enjoy decorating these cookies with icing and candies. #dessert #holiday #baking

Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Line baking sheets with parchment paper.

- Butter | 3/4 cup | 
- Brown Sugar | 3/4 cup | 
- Molasses | 1/2 cup | 
- Egg | 1 | 

In a large bowl, cream together butter, brown sugar, molasses, and egg until smooth.

- Flour | 3 cups | 
- Baking Powder | 1 tsp | 
- Baking Soda | 1/2 tsp | 
- Ground Ginger | 2 tsp | 
- Ground Cinnamon | 1 tsp | 
- Ground Cloves | 1/4 tsp | 
- Salt | 1/2 tsp | 

In another bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, and salt. Gradually blend into the creamed mixture.

Wrap the dough in plastic and let it firm up in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

Roll out dough to about 1/4 inch thickness on a floured surface. Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.

Place cookies about 1 inch apart on the prepared baking sheets.

Bake for 8-10 minutes in the preheated oven, until firm. Remove from baking sheets to cool on wire racks.

Once cool, decorate as desired with icing and candies.
